#: ../../migration-1.0.md:1
msgid "Migrating from 0.5.x to 1.0.0"
msgstr "Migración de 0.5.x a 1.0.0"

#: ../../migration-1.0.md:3
msgid ""
"This guide covers the breaking changes introduced in v1.0.0 and how to "
"update your code."
msgstr ""
"Esta guía cubre los cambios incompatibles introducidos en v1.0.0 y cómo "
"actualizar tu código."

#: ../../migration-1.0.md:6
msgid "`create_invoice()` signature change"
msgstr "Cambio en la firma de `create_invoice()`"

#: ../../migration-1.0.md:8
msgid ""
"The `asset` parameter is no longer the first positional argument and is "
"now optional. `amount` is the first positional argument."
msgstr ""
"El parámetro `asset` ya no es el primer argumento posicional y ahora es "
"opcional. `amount` es el primer argumento posicional."

#: ../../migration-1.0.md:11 ../../migration-1.0.md:52
msgid "**Before (0.5.x):**"
msgstr "**Antes (0.5.x):**"

#: ../../migration-1.0.md:13
msgid ""
"invoice = client.create_invoice(Asset.TON, 1.5)\n"
"\n"
"# or with keyword arguments\n"
"invoice = client.create_invoice(asset=Asset.TON, amount=1.5)\n"
msgstr ""
"invoice = client.create_invoice(Asset.TON, 1.5)\n"
"\n"
"# o con argumentos con nombre\n"
"invoice = client.create_invoice(asset=Asset.TON, amount=1.5)\n"

#: ../../migration-1.0.md:20 ../../migration-1.0.md:59
msgid "**After (1.0.0):**"
msgstr "**Después (1.0.0):**"

#: ../../migration-1.0.md:22
msgid ""
"invoice = client.create_invoice(1.5, asset=Asset.TON)\n"
"\n"
"# keyword-only style still works, but asset must come after amount\n"
"invoice = client.create_invoice(amount=1.5, asset=Asset.TON)\n"
msgstr ""
"invoice = client.create_invoice(1.5, asset=Asset.TON)\n"
"\n"
"# el estilo solo con argumentos con nombre sigue funcionando, pero asset debe ir después de amount\n"
"invoice = client.create_invoice(amount=1.5, asset=Asset.TON)\n"

#: ../../migration-1.0.md:29
msgid ""
"If you were already using `asset=` and `amount=` as keyword arguments, "
"the only change is that `asset` is now optional (required only for crypto"
" invoices)."
msgstr ""
"Si ya estabas usando `asset=` y `amount=` como argumentos con nombre, "
"el único cambio es que `asset` ahora es opcional (requerido solo para "
"facturas de criptomonedas)."

#: ../../migration-1.0.md:32
msgid "Fiat invoices"
msgstr "Facturas en moneda fiat"

#: ../../migration-1.0.md:34
msgid ""
"The signature change enables the new fiat invoice support. To create a "
"fiat invoice, omit `asset` and pass `currency_type`, `fiat`, and "
"`accepted_assets` instead:"
msgstr ""
"El cambio en la firma habilita el nuevo soporte para facturas en moneda "
"fiat. Para crear una factura fiat, omite `asset` y pasa `currency_type`, "
"`fiat` y `accepted_assets` en su lugar:"

#: ../../migration-1.0.md:38
msgid ""
"invoice = client.create_invoice(\n"
"    amount=10.00,\n"
"    currency_type=\"fiat\",\n"
"    fiat=\"USD\",\n"
"    accepted_assets=\"USDT,TON,BTC\",\n"
")\n"
msgstr ""
"invoice = client.create_invoice(\n"
"    amount=10.00,\n"
"    currency_type=\"fiat\",\n"
"    fiat=\"USD\",\n"
"    accepted_assets=\"USDT,TON,BTC\",\n"
")\n"

#: ../../migration-1.0.md:47
msgid "`ExchangeRate.source` is now a `str`"
msgstr "`ExchangeRate.source` ahora es un `str`"

#: ../../migration-1.0.md:49
msgid ""
"`ExchangeRate.source` changed from the `Asset` enum to a plain `str` "
"because the API can return fiat currency codes that are not members of "
"`Asset`."
msgstr ""
"`ExchangeRate.source` cambió del enum `Asset` a un `str` simple "
"porque la API puede devolver códigos de moneda fiat que no son miembros de "
"`Asset`."

#: ../../migration-1.0.md:54
msgid ""
"rates = client.get_exchange_rates()\n"
"btc_usd = next(r for r in rates if r.source == Asset.BTC and r.target == "
"\"USD\")\n"
msgstr ""
"rates = client.get_exchange_rates()\n"
"btc_usd = next(r for r in rates if r.source == Asset.BTC and r.target == "
"\"USD\")\n"

#: ../../migration-1.0.md:61
msgid ""
"rates = client.get_exchange_rates()\n"
"btc_usd = next(r for r in rates if r.source == \"BTC\" and r.target == "
"\"USD\")\n"
msgstr ""
"rates = client.get_exchange_rates()\n"
"btc_usd = next(r for r in rates if r.source == \"BTC\" and r.target == "
"\"USD\")\n"

#: ../../migration-1.0.md:66
msgid "Validation error messages"
msgstr "Mensajes de error de validación"

#: ../../migration-1.0.md:68
msgid ""
"Internal validation was generalized to support checks and transfers. If "
"your code matches on exception messages from `create_invoice` or "
"`get_invoices`, update accordingly:"
msgstr ""
"La validación interna se generalizó para soportar cheques y transferencias. "
"Si tu código compara mensajes de excepción de `create_invoice` o "
"`get_invoices`, actualízalo de la siguiente manera:"

#: ../../migration-1.0.md
msgid "0.5.x message"
msgstr "Mensaje en 0.5.x"

#: ../../migration-1.0.md
msgid "1.0.0 message"
msgstr "Mensaje en 1.0.0"

#: ../../migration-1.0.md
msgid "`\"invoice_ids string cannot be empty\"`"
msgstr "`\"invoice_ids string cannot be empty\"`"

#: ../../migration-1.0.md
msgid "`\"ids string cannot be empty\"`"
msgstr "`\"ids string cannot be empty\"`"

#: ../../migration-1.0.md
msgid "`\"invoice_ids list cannot be empty\"`"
msgstr "`\"invoice_ids list cannot be empty\"`"

#: ../../migration-1.0.md
msgid "`\"ids list cannot be empty\"`"
msgstr "`\"ids list cannot be empty\"`"

#: ../../migration-1.0.md
msgid "`\"invoice_ids string must contain positive integer IDs\"`"
msgstr "`\"invoice_ids string must contain positive integer IDs\"`"

#: ../../migration-1.0.md
msgid "`\"ids string must contain positive integer IDs\"`"
msgstr "`\"ids string must contain positive integer IDs\"`"

#: ../../migration-1.0.md
msgid "`\"invoice_ids list must contain positive integers\"`"
msgstr "`\"invoice_ids list must contain positive integers\"`"

#: ../../migration-1.0.md
msgid "`\"ids list must contain positive integers\"`"
msgstr "`\"ids list must contain positive integers\"`"

#: ../../migration-1.0.md
msgid "`\"invoice_ids must be a comma-separated string or list of integers\"`"
msgstr "`\"invoice_ids must be a comma-separated string or list of integers\"`"

#: ../../migration-1.0.md
msgid "`\"ids must be a comma-separated string or list of integers\"`"
msgstr "`\"ids must be a comma-separated string or list of integers\"`"

#: ../../migration-1.0.md:80
msgid "New endpoints"
msgstr "Nuevos endpoints"

#: ../../migration-1.0.md:82
msgid "These are additive and do not break existing code, but are worth noting:"
msgstr "Estos son aditivos y no rompen el código existente, pero vale la pena mencionarlos:"

#: ../../migration-1.0.md:84
msgid "`delete_invoice(invoice_id)`"
msgstr "`delete_invoice(invoice_id)`"

#: ../../migration-1.0.md:85
msgid "`create_check(asset, amount, ...)` / `delete_check(check_id)`"
msgstr "`create_check(asset, amount, ...)` / `delete_check(check_id)`"

#: ../../migration-1.0.md:86
msgid "`get_checks(...)` with `iter_checks()` and `iter_check_pages()` pagination"
msgstr "`get_checks(...)` con paginación mediante `iter_checks()` e `iter_check_pages()`"

#: ../../migration-1.0.md:87
msgid ""
"`get_transfers(...)` with `iter_transfers()` and `iter_transfer_pages()` "
"pagination"
msgstr ""
"`get_transfers(...)` con paginación mediante `iter_transfers()` e "
